      "writtenOn": "2016-11-17T19:29:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sticking a non-exception into a hole that everyone expects will hold exceptions. Is that the right call?\n\nIs there a more appropriate single exception that we can use to say “this was a signal”, and then stick the signal number in ExceptionInformation?",
      "revId": "e93d9799959897ed628162f44dbeaaf8ebfc8987",
