      "writtenOn": "2016-11-17T19:29:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "ucrt source tells me that signal() is effective per-thread for FPE, not per-process. That…stinks. But like I was saying above, I can’t see why we’d want FPE as a signal anyway, so it might not matter.",
      "revId": "e93d9799959897ed628162f44dbeaaf8ebfc8987",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "90a054a7_77fbc806",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 546,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-11-17T20:36:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmm, yeah. :( That would be a horrible mess to set up API-wise.\n\nI tried signalling from a background thread and it does seem to work, though I\u0027m not sure why given what you found.\n\n...\n\nOh, right. If there\u0027s a signal handler then that\u0027s run, but if there\u0027s not, then it does end up in the unhandled exception filter. (It looked like it worked locally because the signal handler just called the UEF).\n\nI agree that I probably shouldn\u0027t have added the FPE handler then, so I\u0027m going to simplify all this and only add SIGABRT in this CL.",
      "parentUuid": "90a054a7_d79f143a",
      "revId": "e93d9799959897ed628162f44dbeaaf8ebfc8987",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
